  79:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_Tuner.c **** *
  80:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_Tuner.c **** * \brief
  81:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_Tuner.c **** *  Establishes synchronized communication with the Tuner application.
  82:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_Tuner.c **** *
  83:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_Tuner.c **** * \details
  84:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_Tuner.c **** *  This function is used to establish synchronized communication between the
  85:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_Tuner.c **** *  CapSense Component and Tuner application (or other host controllers).
  86:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_Tuner.c **** *  This function is called periodically in the application program loop
  87:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_Tuner.c **** *  to serve the Tuner application (or host controller) requests and commands.
  88:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_Tuner.c **** *  In most cases, the best place to call this function is after processing and
  89:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_Tuner.c **** *  before next scanning.
  90:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_Tuner.c **** *
  91:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_Tuner.c **** *  If this function is absent in the application program, then communication is
  92:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_Tuner.c **** *  asynchronous and the following disadvantages are applicable:
  93:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_Tuner.c **** *    - The raw counts displayed in the tuner may be filtered and/or unfiltered.
  94:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_Tuner.c **** *      As a result, noise and SNR measurements will not be accurate.
  95:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_Tuner.c **** *    - The Tuner tool may read the sensor data such as raw counts from a scan
  96:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_Tuner.c **** *      multiple times, as a result, noise and SNR measurement will not be
  97:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_Tuner.c **** *      accurate.
  98:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_Tuner.c **** *    - The Tuner tool and host controller should not change the Component parameters
  99:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_Tuner.c **** *      via the tuner interface. Changing the Component parameters via the tuner
 100:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_Tuner.c **** *      interface in the async mode will result in Component abnormal behavior.
 101:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_Tuner.c **** *
 102:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_Tuner.c **** *  Note that calling this function is not mandatory for the application, but
 103:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_Tuner.c **** *  required only to synchronize the communication with the host controller or
 104:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_Tuner.c **** *  tuner application.
 105:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_Tuner.c **** *
 106:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_Tuner.c **** * \return
 107:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_Tuner.c **** *  In some cases, the application program may need to know if the Component was
 108:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_Tuner.c **** *  re-initialized. The return indicates if a restart command was executed or not:
 109:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_Tuner.c **** *    - CapSense_STATUS_RESTART_DONE - Based on a received command, the
 110:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_Tuner.c **** *      Component was restarted.
 111:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_Tuner.c **** *    -  CapSense_STATUS_RESTART_NONE - No restart was executed by this
 112:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_Tuner.c **** *      function.
